Class ga_PathFinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.software.reuze.ga_PathFinder

  • public class ga_PathFinder
extends Object
    Finds a path through PathBlockingObstacles. Some code concepts from: http://www.policyalmanac.org/games/aStarTutorial.htm Thanks to Jono and Nate (Nathan Sweet) from JavaGaming.org for their clever help.
    Version:
    20 December 2008
    Author:
    Keith Woodward

      • calc

        public ga_PathData calc(ga_Vector2 start,
               ga_Vector2 end,
               float maxTempNodeConnectionDist,
               float maxSearchDistStartToEnd,
               ga_PathNodeConnector nodeConnector,
               List obstacles)
        Parameters:
        start -
        end -
        maxTempNodeConnectionDist - Maximum connection distance from start to obstacles and end to obstacles. The smaller the distance, the faster the algorithm.
        maxSearchDistStartToEnd - Maximum distance from start to end. Any paths with a longer distance won't be returned. The smaller the value the faster the algorithm.
        nodeConnector -
        obstacles -
        pointList - Path points from start to end. If there was no path found, or no path found with a distance less than maxSearchDistStartToEnd, an empty (zero-size) list will be returned.
        Returns:

        public ga_PathData calc(ga_Vector2 start,
               ga_Vector2 end,
               float maxTempNodeConnectionDist,
               float maxSearchDistStartToEnd,
               ga_PathNodeConnector nodeConnector,
               ga_TileArray obstaclesTileArray)
        Parameters:
        start -
        end -
        maxTempNodeConnectionDist - Maximum connection distance from start to obstacles and end to obstacles. The smaller the distance, the faster the algorithm.
        maxSearchDistStartToEnd - Maximum distance from start to end. Any paths with a longer distance won't be returned. The smaller the value the faster the algorithm. Use Double.MAX_VALUE to have a very large search dist.
        nodeConnector -
        obstaclesTileArray -
        pointList - Path points from start to end. If there was no path found, or no path found with a distance less than maxSearchDistStartToEnd, an empty (zero-size) list will be returned.
